‘If you have as much as a 10 per cent reduction in body weight during the race, you get the effects of heat stroke — loss of vision and lack of reactions. We want to keep it to under a five per cent reduction.

‘So he will have a pre-race drink made up of carbohydrates, electrolytes — minerals such as sodium — and protein.

