‘His supply for the race is contained in a kind of bladder. It is one of the last things to go into the car to keep it as cold as possible for as long as possible. 

'He will get the drink by pressing the drinks button on the steering wheel. It goes through a series of tubes and through a hole in his balaclava into his mouth.

‘The drink will get extremely hot as the race goes on but it will still be beneficial to him.

‘He will then have a recovery drink over the four to six hours after the race. It is a slightly different composition — higher in carbohydrates, proteins and fats.’

